verses.roman:
dui mālā govinda dui-jane parāila
advaita, avadhūta-gosāñi baḍa sukha pāila

synonyms: dui mālā—the two garlands; govinda—Govinda; dui-jane parāila—placed on the necks of two personalities; advaita—Advaita Ācārya; avadhūta-gosāñi—Nityānanda Prabhu; baḍa sukha pāila—became very happy.
translation: Govinda offered the two garlands to Advaita Ācārya and Nityānanda Prabhu, and They both became very happy.
